reviews.review_text: Grate Show - I was there!! I can't believe I ran across this jem! One of the best shows of 1990 summer tour! The balloons and kind veggie burritos were everywhere in the city park after the show.

too hot what a great show this was  must've been 110 degrees  the fire department puulled up a bunch of firetrucks and opened up the hoses straight into the air  by the front gates about 3 in the afternoon  they gave away drinking water and danced in the artificial rain with us all afternoon  then the dead opened with cold rain & snow  couldnt think of a better way to spend the 4th  miss you jerry  god bless the archive

7-4-90 Nice show. Good remaster by Charlie. If you have a little 30 watt shelf stereo like me the levels are low and the bass is particularly thin. If you have a high powered stereo with a subwoofrer I'm sure this will sound great.

110 That is how hot it was when the show started only time I saw Phil and Jerry in shorts. The first set was ok, The Scarlet>Fire was great. After drums was a standard list but played very well. The Fire on the Mountain was the best I've seen really hot like the day
loved this show came from New Jersey had to much fun ,did the whole tour,only thing is this is a little low..But i love the tapers and get that

great show, little hot until the sun went down. One of my first shows, what a great set list, the played Fire on the Mountain for ever it seemed like.  Jerry and Phil were sporting cut offs and man were those legs white.  Love ya Jer!

What fixation feeds this fever I gotta admit I get jealous when I read about all your first person recollections of being at this show. I only got to see the band after Vince took over the Hot Seat. If I had only known just a little sooner about what I'd been missing out on I'm sure I could've managed to catch a show or two around this time. 
This isn't the best of the shows from this tour but the recording while it has its flaws is decent and the pre-Drums segment features some excellent playing from Brent and Phil. Brent was a beast no matter what his detractors say. Slowly he's becoming my favorite of all the musicians who have sat on the bench over the years. 
There are some spotty vocals which cost some points when it comes to ratings and as I mentioned there are some flaws with the sound while overall it does sound better than some other posted stuff I've come across, (which I want to thank all the people who've given the masses free access to this material out of the sheer love of it, I love all you guys). The set list is great, I mean I wouldn't have been able to ask for much more.l, but I want to be fair in rating shows I rate and overall this is average for the time but it's got its moments

Last of the Best I got to see GD 14 more times after this show but this one was the best of the last 6 years. Took the drummer in the band I was in at the time and his girlfriend ( their first Dead show ) along with my wife to this show. The day and the music were both hot. Vividly remember start of second set with Bobby's Victim or Crime into Jerry's Foolish Heart and then Jerry looking over his glasses at Brent and nodding it's your turn and they jam into Brent's Just a Little Light. Then remember being home about 2 weeks later and hearing Brent was dead. So sad! Though I never saw Pigpen, my favorite shows were in the Brent era. I miss Jerry and Brent. Thank you

First Dead Show and SO HOT! I had been turned on to the Dead by my buddy Randy. Through commercial releases and bootleg tapes he got me up to speed for this show. Oh my goodness! It was SO HOT that Fourth of July day. Jerry came out in shorts and I thought I heard a collective "gasp" from the crowd. We were sitting in the lawn section about 40 feet behind the "taper section". I had never seen anything like this and trust me I'd been to lots of concerts. I like to listen to this show on days when I need a good flashback. When they opened with Cold Rain and Snow we all just looked and each other and laughed! At that moment... it sounded as if they were ordering that up for us. There are a few hiccups here and there but who cares?! This was the only show that I got the see Brent play and he was killing Just a Little Light that night. He spaces a line but makes up for it with the heart he put into the singing. Then right into Scarlet Begonias and that was it for me! I forgot where I was until US Blues came around and we thought it was time for the fireworks! Well that didn't happen but there was sure a good show put on by the Heads in the parking lot. Thank you Randy. Miss you, Jerry, and Brent. Download the Live Concert version so you have your own copy. Oh! I nearly forgot that this is my favorite version of The Wheel that I've heard. Keep on Truckin'.
Su90 Tour N1- Final July 4th Show  Good July 4th outing, with a mighty fine third quarter: Victim->Foolish Heart->Little Light->Scarlet->Fire. Brent going off on Fire.
